name: GrowthCurve
description: Grow up cells and read every interval

src_info.label: Sample Sources
src_info.description: Sample Source Selection. Up to 94 wells may be selected on a plate to leave space for two controls.

inoc_info.label: Overnight Parameters
inoc_info.description: Select culture and media volumes for inoculation

inc_time_1.label: Initial Outgrowth Time
inc_time_1.description: Select the incubation time, must be between 12 and 24.

recovery_info.label: Recovery Parameters
recovery_info.description: Select culture and media volumes for recovery. This will be the starting volume of the growth curve culture.

read_info.label: Sampling Interval
read_info.description: Select total incubation time and sampling for growth curve reading.

sample_points.label: Sampling Times
sample_points.description: Specify a comma-separated list of integers, representing hours to sample at. A maximum of 9 can be specified.

sampling_info.label: Measurement Volume Parameters
sampling_info.description: Specify volume and solvent for plate read.

read_cult_vol.label: Volume of Culture to Plate Read

read_solv_vol.label: Volume of Solvent to Plate Read

read_solv.label: Read Solvent
read_solv.description: Select Solvent to Resuspend Cells in for Plate Read

list_of_gains.description: Specify up to three gains to read at. If fewer reads are required, set gains equal to each other.
list_of_gains.label: Gain Parameters

validate_samples.label: Validate Samples Contain ID
validate_samples.description: Validates each source sample has a `sd2_common_name` or `sbh_uri` property.

experiment_id.label: Experiment ID
experiment_id.description: Experimental Request ID to be associated with data generated.
